Rocky will be euthanized by his owners on Friday by their vet at 9am if someone does not step up and save him. We have been given permission to share the letter below his owner provided to us along with contact her information. Please read, share and if you’re able, please contact revivo.andrea@gmail.com to save him. Please also keep communications positive and focussed on the dog as this is likely his last hope. Thank you. He is located in LOS ANGELES AREA

Per Rocky’s owner
“Rocky is an amazing and loving pit mix who needs a new home. We rescued Rocky about 4 years ago. We’ve had the privilege of being his family until now. As a rescue, Rocky is a fearful dog and that makes it a little challenging having him around wild / active toddlers. As much as it breaks our hearts, with our growing family, we need to find him a new and loving home. 

He follows commands like sit, stay, heel. He hardly barks at other dogs. He’s the ideal pup for someone looking for a best friend but not for someone with young kids running around. He is crate and muzzle trained. 

We have been trying to find him a home for the last year. Unfortunately, we are unable to care for him anymore. We have an appointment at the vet this Friday at 9am to put him down but we are desperately trying to find an alternative solution for rocky.

We believe more than anything that he can do very well in a home that better suits him. But he does pose a risk to our kids and we have been living on edge that one little mistake can trigger an accident. It’s become very difficult. I appreciate your help and hope very much that someone steps up. He is a wonderful dog who deserves a better life than we are able to provide.”

#standupforpits

If you truly love acting. If you miss the small independent movies that focus on story and performance. I beg you to see TO LESLIE!!! Andrea Riseboroughs performance is heartbreaking, riveting and important. Michael Morris’ direction is what every actors hopes for when collaborating with a director. He gives Riseborough the room, the air, the patience to bring Leslie to life. You feel what she feels and so much more. In addition to Riseboroughs brilliant performance and Morris’ profound direction the rest of the cast is extraordinary. Not a false note by anyone EVER! They don’t make movies like this anymore and they need to!  I’ve missed getting lost in the characters rather than the special effects. Seek out TO LESLIE. You can watch it on Amazon.

🚨🆘MEDICALLY ALERTED & URGENT! 1 YEAR OLD BOMBIES MUST EXIT SHELTER BY TUESDAY 2/7 at 4PM!!🆘🚨

Our baby girl Bombies is another pup out of time! She arrived at the shelter as a stray in December. Sadly, she’s had a hard time adjusting to shelter life. Our first time meeting her, we found her screaming in her kennel because she had climbed the walls and was unable to get down. She had cut her paw in the process. When we helped her down and took her to the yard, she started to relax. She’s being kept inside now, so volunteers have only been able to see her a handful of times, but we’ve found she’s a very sweet girl who definitely seems happiest when hanging out with her human friends!

She’s been able to make it into playgroup twice. The first time in, she was described as playful and social. The second time, she was more selective and asked for space from the other pups. Both times it was noted she was anxious.

Due to her stress at the shelter, she only has until TUESDAY 2/7 at 4PM to be ADOPTED or RESCUED (rescues need FOSTERS!)! Please consider being Bombies’s hero! Contact South LA Shelter IMMEDIATELY if you can help her!

Bombies, #A2063225
1 yr old, ~44 lbs

MEDICAL ALERTS:
•	SHOWING HIGH FEAR, ANXIETY & STRESS IN SHELTER INJURING HERSELF

Ok so now that I’ve recovered from the finale of @millionlittlethingsabc here’s my story…5 years ago both my parents passed away and a couple of months later I got an audition for this show about a group of friends and I was going to audition for one of the characters mother. The rest of you crazies @stephshortstak @allisonemiller @mrgiuntoli @jamesroday thank you for always welcoming me with open arms and making me laugh. I so wish we could have played more!!!! @florianalima @officialchanceh @cameronesposito @thesampancake I so wish we could have gotten to play!

The amazing @tarakarsian and I spent the day volunteering at iatse headquarters passing out food so that members of the teamsters and Iatse could have a Thanksgiving meal with their families. We were passing out food and diapers. They were all so grateful to be given some help of some kind. They don’t have a strike fund and most of their unemployment is running out or has already run out. One person said she know of 8 evictions and 7 foreclosures. It was sobering and heart wrenching. They have stood by us and with us but they need to get back to work. We can make that happen. Oh and we also met #LindsayDougherty. I have a full on girl crush

Every Tuesday I am celebrating actors I love!
 
Today I am spotlighting Romy Rosemont, an actress who has captivated me with her unique performances for decades. When you look at her resume it truly feels like she has done it all. She can play warmth and vulnerability, malice and cunning, and she has a wicked sense of humor too. Most importantly she leads with kindness and respect.

Now Romy shares some tips with you:

1. You have to LOVE acting more than anything else or it’s not worth it, because the hard times and rejection that can come from pursuing an acting career can really suck. Unless, you really love it and you can’t imagine doing anything else.

2. HAVE FUN! Acting can be challenging and frustrating and intense and transformative and so much f’ing fun. We get paid to play dress up. So PLEASE remember, have fun when you’re working. When I’m in a show or a movie or a play, I connect so much better to the characters when I know the actors are having a blast.

3. I always make a playlist that in some way relates to what I’m working on. I find music really helpful when I’m doing an emotional scene. When I have to cry in a scene and they need me to do it quickly the right song
can get me there. It’s my little shortcut but the emotion is authentic.

4. DON’T BE A DICK! A TV or film set is filled with the most amazing people and NO ONE wants to be around anyone who’s making everything harder. Be kind, hang up your clothes when you change out of your wardrobe, don’t be late, don’t make people wait, respect every department because it takes a village. DON’T BE A DICK!

Thank you Romy for sharing with us! Please check out her bio in the comments section below.
